User Management & OTP Service API
This project is a backend API for user management, including features for creating users, sending OTPs via SMS or email, updating user data, managing drivers, and handling user credits. The API is built with Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, and includes validation middleware for request input.

Features
User Registration: Create new users with phone, email, and name.

OTP Services:
Send OTP to user phone via SMS.
Send OTP to user email.

User Management:
Get user information.
Update user data.
Update user credit information.
Delete user account.

Driver Management:
Get driver information.
Update driver details.

Clone the repository:

git clone <repository-url>
cd <project-folder>


Install dependencies:
npm install


Create a .env file with your environment variables (MongoDB URI, SMS/Email API keys, etc.):

INFOBIP_API_KEY=56f0300fae690d9a005431f6228e00bf-a207de37-5f8f-47d4-8945-a994eeb6e4e9
VONAGE_API_KEY=26e5cea4
VONAGE_API_SECRET='L4jw)sMQxs*Kqtucje'
VONAGE_FROM=NEXMO

Start the server:
npm run dev


Server will run at http://localhost:1200 (or your configured port).

Project Structure
├── routes/
│   └── user.js         # User-related API routes
├── service/
│   └── user/           # Business logic for user operations
├── validation/         # Request validation schemas
├── utils/              # Helper functions and validation middleware
├── app.js / server.js  # Express app entry point

Dependencies

express – Web framework
mongoose – MongoDB ODM
axios – HTTP client (for SMS/Email APIs)
dotenv – Environment variable management
joi – Input validation
vonage – SMS API integration
cors – Cross-origin requests
nodemailer – Email service

Usage

To create a new user:

POST /user
Body: {
  "phoneNumber": "+201234567890",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "name": "John Doe"
}


To send OTP to phone:

POST /user/OTP
Body: {
  "to": "+201234567890"
}


To send OTP to email:

POST /user/OTPEmail
Body: {
  "email": "user@example.com"
}